This article is a notice from the President of the United States, Barack Obama, regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to certain terrorist attacks. The President states that he is continuing the national emergency, which was initially declared on September 14, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. The President explains that the terrorist threat is ongoing and therefore, the national emergency and the powers and authorities adopted to deal with it must continue beyond September 14, 2011. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.